  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Content Creator",
  "description": "<p>Job Scope:</p><ul><li>Design digital and print assets including social media graphics, posters, menus, packaging, and more</li></ul><ul><li>Create short-form content such as Instagram Reels, TikToks, and animated stories (with guidance and support from the marketing team)</li></ul><ul><li>Support seasonal campaigns, new product launches, and brand events through creative visual assets</li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with the marketing team on brainstorming and visual direction</li></ul><ul><li>Assist with photo/video shoots and perform basic photo/video editing</li></ul><ul><li>Stay up to date on design trends and social content formats to keep our brands fresh and relevant</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure brand consistency across all touchpoints and platforms</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>What We’re Looking For</p><ul><li>Diploma or degree in Graphic Design, Visual Communications, or related fields</li></ul><ul><li>Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign; Premiere Pro or After Effects is a plus)</li></ul><ul><li>Basic knowledge of short-form video editing tools like CapCut or Premiere Pro</li><li>Strong layout and typography skills with a keen eye for aesthetics</li><li>Familiar with trends on Instagram, TikTok, and food/lifestyle content</li><li>Positive team player with a willingness to learn and experiment</li><li>Interest in food, youth culture and Korean trends is a plus</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Why Join Us?</p><ul><li>You’ll work on multiple exciting F&B brands, each with its own creative style and audience</li></ul><ul><li>Be part of a nimble team that values bold design and original content</li></ul><ul><li>Gain hands-on experience across design, social media, and content production</li><li>Enjoy food tastings, fun shoots, and a work culture that celebrates creativity (and good food)<br /><br />Working Hours : 9am to 6pm<br />Working Location: Kaki Bukit</li></ul>",
